  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219875/Lama_Emission_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219875/Lama_Emission_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"720\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219896\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Lama_Emission_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219875\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"674905ad-04be-4207-97a0-b5773357e1e0\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Emission, or glow, can make an object </span><em>appear</em><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\"> to emit light. </span><br/><br/><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">This is useful when you need a textured effect like lit panels, circuitry, lava, or other complex effects with local influence in lighting. Since these materials do not truly emit light, indirect lighting is used to achieve the effect that this material is influencing its surroundings. No bump or normal mapping is available because the effect would not be seen either here or in reality.</span></p><p><br/></p><h3 id=\"LamaEmission-EmissionParameters\"><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">Emission Parameters</span></h3><p><strong>Color</strong></p><p>This is the result of a flat color or a signal from a texture or procedural pattern used to drive the effect. The color black is essentially &quot;off&quot; or no effect.<br/><br/></p><hr/><p>In this example, a texture is plugged into the Color input.  The TV lines are created using PxrPhasorNoise and both the texture and PhasorNoise offset's are animated over time to create the glowing holographic billboard.</p><p><br/></p><div class=\"embeddedObject conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"d2532927-9dff-4d0b-8060-955862a3b899\" data-macro-id=\"1dff4514-379f-410b-8ab4-205d46763973\" data-macro-name=\"multimedia\">\n    <video src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/542219875/Lama_Emission_example.mp4\" height=\"380\" width=\"100%\" controls=\"\">\n        Your browser does not support the HTML5 video element\n</video>\n\n</div><p><br/><br/></p><hr/><p><br/></p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" height=\"64\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219875/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219875/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219902\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManFundamentals_logo.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219875\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"6b1780e7-0ef7-4538-ad47-466f962d75d1\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219875/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219875/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330554686&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64 1x\"></span><br/><strong>RenderMan Fundamentals</strong></p><p><br/></p><iframe align=\"middle\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"dcdceb62-9940-4df7-833b-3a6c215ee1c0\" data-macro-id=\"a1a67358869b1abcd800727e84b38da08b912beadf10bd6bd04422977e3d7982\" data-macro-name=\"iframe\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-forms allow-modals allow-orientation-lock allow-pointer-lock allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-presentation allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation\" scrolling=\"yes\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/604779917?h=d9fe405f6b&amp;title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"960\">\n    \n</iframe>\n<p><br/></p><hr/><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br/></p>"
